Join us for the Second Annual Camo for a Cause 5K! You can expect a beautiful course mapped out along the water, lots of fun booths and vendors, music on the trail to keep you pumped as well as SDSU cheer leaders and Girl Scouts from a local troop, camo face painting station, bounce house for the kids, and of course festive Camo for a Cause 5k t-shirts, camo bandana, bibs, and finisher medals for all participant. Special medals for first man and woman!

100% of the proceeds goes directly back to supporting our mission.

The Unbattle Project (UP) is a non-profit organization that offers free confidential counseling to men and women in the military. We believe that service members and veterans are “bent, not broken”. We want to help them get back to their lives by providing no-cost therapy in order to reduce the likelihood of homelessness and suicide.

Did you know that 1 in 5 veterans of the Iraq and Afghanistan wars are diagnosed with PTSD and/or depression and that over 50% of homeless veterans have mental health issues? Did you also know that 20 veterans commit suicide each day and that veterans make up 20% of U.S. suicides? San Diego is known for being a military town. In fact, there are over 100,000 active duty and 240,500 veterans residing in San Diego County. It is very important that we get these men and women the help they need. If left untreated, many military men and women with mental health issues will continue to struggle to keep jobs. Consequently, these veterans end up on the streets, adding to our growing homeless population. 

Event details and schedule

Schedule:

7:30AM Check-in/packet pick-up

8:15-8:30 Group Warm up

8:45AM Color Guard, Anthem, and a warm welcome to all our wonderful participants 

9:00AM 5K Begins (5 Kilometers=3.1 miles)

11:00AM Course Closer and Ending Announcments 

included:

Soft cotton t-shirt

Bib number

Finisher medal for first man and woman

Festive bandana

Tax write off

Parking/Arrival:

This event will be held between Dewey Rd and Roosevelt Rd. along Cushing Rd. There is plenty of free lot and street parking.

We recommend that you arrive 1.5 hours before the start of the event to allow adequate time for parking, packet pickup and warmup

Packet Pick-up:

March 23rd from 4:00-7:00pm

Point Loma Sports Club 
2751 Roosevelt Rd
San Diego, CA 92106

What to Bring:

Water and a photo ID for check-in

What to Wear:

Wear comfortable running shoes and anything camo! Wear a camo tutu, bandana, or paint your face! Have fun with it and get creative!!

THE EDCO SAN DIEGO LEGENDS 5K is a family-friendly event celebrating San Diego's rich sports history that will include games, activities and fun for everyone. By registering for one of these events you will receive an all-inclusive package featuring:

Participants will receive:

  • Opportunity to walk/run along the water in NTC Park at Liberty Station in Point Loma
  • 5K Walk/Fun run including chip timing for 5K by Race Timers (Kids Fun Run will not be chip timed)
  • Commemorative event finisher medal
  • Commemorative performance shirt

After the races participants can enjoy:

  • Autograph Booth - featuring current/former San Diego Sports Legends and local celebrities**
  • Free Drink and Snacks
  • Kids Fun Zone - Featuring bounce houses from L.B. Jumpers Express, games and contests 
  • Awards Presentation - Ceremony to present the top three overall male and female finishers 

 

 *Certain Restrictions Apply, While Supplies Last

 **Please note: Celebrities will be available for autographs following the race. No memorabilia is permitted on the premises and will not be authorized for signatures/autograph. Race bib required for autographs.

Event details and schedule

 Friday, June 8, 2018

  • Race Packet Pick Up
    • 12:00 p.m. - 6:00 p.m.
    • Road Runner Sports - 5553 Copley Dr., San Diego, CA 92111 

 

Saturday, June 9, 2018

  • Registration Begins at 6:45 a.m.
  • Race Start Time: 5K Start time: 8:15 a.m.
  • Kids 1-mile Fun Run:  9:00 a.m.

Wave Academy is hosting WAVES FOR THE BRAVE 5K Trail Run & Hike. This event honors veterans who are bravely overcoming the challenges of post-traumatic stress and promotes mental health therapy in our community. More than 20 percent of all veterans in San Diego are dealing with post traumatic stress, totaling about 11,000 men and women. 

The timed 3.1 mile route follows a well-maintained dirt trail that loops around the lake with beautiful views. The event begins and ends in the grassy, shady park next to the lake. The 5K route goes clock-wise around the lake. Water is available at the start/finish and at 2 miles. 

Register as an individual, veteran, youth, team captain or team member.

Sponsor the event and be recognized for supporting veterans and mental health in our community. 

 

RAISE FOR THE BRAVE

You can make a difference by raising funds that support healing through water for veterans. Get your team to raise funds together, or fundraise as an individual. Prizes will be given to the top fundraising individual and fundraising team.

BENEFICIARY

Proceeds support Wave Academy’s program of warm water therapy sessions for qualifying veterans. 

THANK YOU FOR MAKING A DIFFERENCE

Thank you for enhancing the quality of life for San Diego’s veterans, supporting mental health, and our community!

Event details and schedule

TIMELINE

6:30am – On-site registration and bib pick-up opens

7:00am – Parking lot at Poway High School opens with bus transportation to start (1 mile distance)

8:00am – Race starts for runners, hikers follow

9:00am – Awards & Recognition

TRANSPORTATION & PARKING

Park at Lake Poway: Poway residents and active-duty military (with ID) are free. Non-residents pay $10.

Park at Poway High School: Free parking is available at Poway High School. It is 1.25 miles from the school to the start of the race. Bus transportation starts at 7am and will loop every 10-15 minutes.

AWARDS 

Awards will be given in these categories: 

  • Top three overall female and male finishers (1st, 2nd 3rd)
  • Top three overall veteran female and male finishers (1st, 2nd, 3rd)
  • Top three youth (0-17) female and male finishers (1st, 2nd, 3rd)
  • Top fundraising individual and top fundraising team

SWAG

  • All participants will receive soft, cotton t-shirts and custom finisher medals.
  • Enjoy post-finish refreshments and snacks
  • Visit booths and tables with resources for a healthy community

City Running Tours - San Diego

Choose how far you would like to run, what areas and sight you would like to see and we will customize a run for you. Your running guide will meet you where you are staying to take you on your run.

We will run at your pace, provide water and bring a camera in case you feel like capturing the moment. Once your run is complete your running guide will return you back where you are staying.

More Details

The cost of your City Running Tour is dependent on the distance selected and number of runners registered. It is full price for 1 runner and 10% off each additional runner. The discount will be automatically deducted.

If you are registering for more than one run you will receive $10 off on the 2nd run and $20 off on the 3rd run. Please make sure to select how many runners. For multiple runners the 10% discount per runner will automatically be deducted.

PLEASE READ

ONCE YOU REGISTER FOR YOUR RUN YOUR CONFIRMATION EMAIL WILL READ AS IF YOUR RUN IS SCHEDULED FOR 12/31/18. PLEASE IGNORE THIS, WE WILL CONTACT YOU TO CONFIRM THE DETAILS OF YOUR RUN.

Fees

$75 for a run up to 6 miles; $5 for each additional mile. There is a 10% discount per runner for each additional runner registered.

Get your Groove on as we race along this scenic waterfront course in San Diego on Saturday, March3 1, 2018.

Girls on the Go Half Marathon, 10K, 5K in San Diego on May 13, 2018 is the place to make a memory with your girlfriend brigade of friends, mothers, daughters and grandmas and run,walk or samba to the finish line. The scenic course begins at Mission Bay Park and takes you along the Ocean front of San Diego Bay and Fiesta Island. Views of the water in every direction.  The course is mostly flat  and paved.  Events include Half Marathon - 10k - 5k and a kid's dash for the young ones.  ALL finishers receive a custom medal unique to the event.  Half marathon participants receive technical shirt and 10k and 5k Women's race T-shirts.  Enjoy refreshments and the celebratory joy of over a thousand women at the finish line festival. Men are welcome to register and support the women in their life.  

Event details and schedule

Celebrate spring in San Diego! GIRLS ON THE GO gives mothers, daughters and girlfriends a chance to run wild during a day of inspiration and fitness. Lively music and a post-race dance party await finishers. 

So grab your girlfriend brigade and register today! Participants receive: A Girlicious shirt and GOTG custom medal unique to the event.

Please note:Registrations are non-refundable or transferable.

Online registration for close at 7pm - Friday 5-11-2018
